Review: Surprised at how along for the ride I was for the beginning! Then unfortunately it drops the ball halfway through and spends the rest of the time doing an unearned touchdown celebration
All buildup, no payoff. Makes sense the Obamas EP’d this.
Immediately in 2023 top 5 for me. Everyone’s very good but Charles Melton is great, imagine being on Riverdale and then dropping this…
I wanted like 20% more characterization of these people but otherwise so sweet. Watched theater camp a day later and laughed at the line “you’re an old soul. This is your last life.”
Exercising instead of facing your emotions way before it was cool
Prequel to the SNL sketch where Kate McKinnon is abducted by aliens
the production design of the foreign country was cool
Sooooo 2002 and I love that about it

The parts where it’s a subjective look at how someone grapples with having done something so enormous are incredible. Hewing so closely to “how it really happened” hurts the movie. Less realism! More movie magic!

Movie: Indiana Jones and the Dial of Destiny
Review: Never had I ever been more sure a movie would end with Phoebe Waller-Bridge putting on the Indiana Jones hat
Kinda was nothing to me, unfortunately. Even despite the chapter headings I was checking my watch. Top little guy of the year but the total was less than the sum of its parts.
